    <Property Name="targetCycleTime" Id="{00ba80c0-ada5-427e-96a3-9bdb8c351a97}">
      <Declaration><![CDATA[(* 
## Short summary

This property can be used to set and read the current target cycle time for a product cycle of a single part.
The target cycle time will be written into every measurement entry and is used to mark cycle time exceedances.

.. <legal notes>

legal notes
=================
| SPDX-FileCopyrightText: © 2025 ekvip automation GmbH <info@ekvip.de>
| SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0
| For details check: Apache-2.0_

.. _Apache-2.0: https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

.. </legal notes>

*)
PROPERTY targetCycleTime : LTIME
]]></Declaration>
      <Get Name="Get" Id="{4e8a7b3f-7676-4747-9d94-094f61a93fba}">
        <Declaration><![CDATA[VAR
END_VAR
]]></Declaration>
        <Implementation>
          <ST><![CDATA[targetCycleTime := THIS^.configuredTargetCycleTime;]]></ST>
        </Implementation>
      </Get>
      <Set Name="Set" Id="{a4f0cf7e-2142-4a26-a365-27c7ece0a749}">
        <Declaration><![CDATA[VAR
END_VAR
]]></Declaration>
        <Implementation>
          <ST><![CDATA[THIS^.configuredTargetCycleTime := targetCycleTime;]]></ST>
        </Implementation>
      </Set>
    </Property>
